MOUNTAIN HOUSE MUSLIM ASSOCIATION
Website Redesign &amp; Masjid Fundraising Project Plan
Prepared for: MHMA Web Developer
Date: May 2026
Version: 1.0
Site: mhma.us

This document outlines the required improvements to mhma.us based on a competitive analysis of
five peer Islamic center websites. Given that MHMA is actively fundraising for the Islamic Center of
Mountain House construction project, the redesign must prioritize conversion-focused fundraising
features while modernizing the overall user experience.

1. Executive Summary
MHMA&#39;s current website serves as a basic informational page but falls significantly behind peer
institutions in three critical areas: fundraising infrastructure, user experience, and content
organization. With an active $8.5M Islamic Center construction campaign underway, the website is
a primary donor touchpoint and must be elevated to match the ambition of the project.
Key Gaps Identified:
• No dedicated, high-impact construction/fundraising campaign page
• No live donation progress tracker or fundraising goal visualization
• No pledge system for donors not ready to give immediately
• No events calendar — a fundamental feature on every peer site
• No newsletter/email capture — critical for donor stewardship
• No programs directory — MHMA has many programs but they are buried
• Prayer times appear duplicated and are not auto-synced
• Homepage hero section lacks visual impact and a clear call to action
Benchmark Sites Reviewed:
• VRIC.org — Valley Ranch Islamic Center (strong programs architecture, monthly sustainers)
• NuecesMosque.com/reconstruction — Best-in-class fundraising campaign page with FAQ,
stats, pledge option
• IrvingMasjid.org — Strong content depth, multiple giving options, good outreach sections
• MCCEastBay.org — Excellent events calendar, services taxonomy, modern layout
• MCABayArea.org — Strong campus expansion integration, newsletter, social proof

