3. Masjid Construction Campaign Page
This is the single most important deliverable. NuecesMosque.com/reconstruction is the gold
standard. MHMA needs a dedicated, standalone campaign page — not just a section within an
existing page — that serves as the hub for all construction fundraising activity.
3.1 Page URL
Recommended: mhma.us/build — or mhma.us/islamic-center (update/expand existing page)
3.2 Required Components
Hero Section
• Full-width architectural rendering or site plan image of the future Islamic Center
• Bold headline: e.g., &#39;Build the Islamic Center of Mountain House&#39;
• Campaign tagline, e.g., &#39;Whoever builds a masjid for the sake of Allah...&#39;
• Two CTAs: [Donate Now] and [Pledge to Give]
Live Fundraising Progress Bar
• Display: Amount Raised / Total Goal ($8.5M)
• Animated progress bar, updated at least weekly (manual update is fine initially)
• Donor count or number of families who have contributed
• Reference: NuecesMosque.com shows this prominently
Project Overview Section
• Brief narrative: Why we need a masjid, community growth in Mountain House
• Key stats: estimated sq footage, projected capacity, community impact numbers
• Embed or link to project brochure PDF
• Embed a vision/campaign video if available (YouTube embed)
Giving Tiers / Campaign Milestones
• Display giving tiers with named levels (e.g., Platinum: $50K+, Gold: $25K+)
• Show construction milestones: Phase 1 Foundation = $X, Phase 2 Structure = $Y
• VRIC uses an &#39;Ansar Club&#39; monthly sustainer model — consider MHMA equivalent
Multiple Giving Options
• Online card via Stripe (already in use — keep)
• Zelle (with designated email, e.g., build@mhma.us or treasurer@mhma.us)
• Check payable to MHMA — show mailing address
• Employer matching / Benevity information
• Crypto donation option (optional Phase 2)
• Waqf / endowment giving note if applicable
Pledge System
• Add a [Pledge to Give] button — links to a simple Google Form or embedded form

• Pledge form fields: Name, Email, Amount, Timeframe (e.g., within 30/60/90 days)
• Pledges collected to separate tracking list; board can follow up
• Display: &#39;Not ready to donate? Pledge now and we&#39;ll remind you.&#39;
FAQ Section
• Model after NuecesMosque.com FAQ — accordion/expandable format
• Sample questions: What is the project vision? What does the building include? Are donations
tax-deductible? Is Zakat eligible? When does construction start? How are funds managed?
• Include MHMA 501(c)(3) EIN number for donor receipts
Testimonials / Community Voices
• 3–5 short community member quotes about why the masjid matters
• Photo + name + brief description (e.g., &#39;Mountain House resident since 2015&#39;)
Email / Update Signup
• &#39;Stay updated on the project&#39; — email capture form
• Connect to Mailchimp, ConvertKit, or existing email platform
• Send quarterly construction updates

4. Homepage Redesign
4.1 Hero Section
The current hero is text-only with no compelling imagery. Every peer site uses a high-quality full-
width photo or video background. MHMA should use either a photo of the current Unity Center
community gathered, or the architectural rendering of the future Islamic Center during the
fundraising campaign.
• Full-width hero image or video (autoplay, muted)
• Clear tagline (current tagline is good — keep &#39;Strengthening the Bond of Brotherhood&#39;)
• Two primary CTAs: [Build Our Masjid] and [Make a Donation] — prominently placed
• Remove duplicate prayer time blocks (currently shows prayer times twice on homepage)
4.2 Prayer Times Widget
• Single, clean prayer times block — adhan and iqamah columns
• Integrate with MasjidAl, IslamicFinder, or similar auto-sync API for automatic updates
• Show today&#39;s date in both Gregorian and Hijri calendar
• Jumma khateeb name and time displayed clearly
4.3 Fundraising Banner / Campaign Strip
• Persistent banner above or below the hero with the masjid fundraising goal
• Mini progress bar showing % raised toward $8.5M goal
• Link to the full campaign page
• Should remain visible even after scrolling (sticky option or early placement)
4.4 Events Section
• Replace the current &#39;Activities and Events&#39; carousel with a full events grid or list
• Show upcoming 4–6 events with date, time, title, brief description, and [Learn More] link
• [View Full Calendar] button linking to a dedicated events page
• Reference: MCCEastBay.org and MCABayArea.org both execute this well
4.5 Programs Snapshot
• Add a &#39;Our Programs&#39; section to the homepage with icon-based cards
• Cards for: Maktab, MHMA Hoops, Iqraa Arabic Academy, Little Explorers, Women&#39;s
Committee, Quran Quest
• [View All Programs] button
4.6 Community Stats
• Add a social proof stats bar (numbers speak to donors and new members)
• Example: Years Serving Community | Families | Youth in Programs | Raised for Masjid

5. Site Architecture &amp; Navigation
The current navigation is minimal: Home | MHMA | Programs | Donate | Login. It does not reflect the
breadth of MHMA&#39;s activities. The redesigned navigation should be organized around user intent.
5.1 Recommended Navigation Structure
Primary Nav:
• Home
• Build Our Masjid ← New, prominent link
• Programs (dropdown: All Programs, Maktab, MHMA Hoops, Iqraa Arabic, Little Explorers,
Women&#39;s Committee)
• Prayer Times
• Events
• About (dropdown: Mission, Board, Committees, Bylaws)
• Donate (primary CTA button style, gold)
5.2 New Pages Required
• mhma.us/build — Islamic Center Campaign Page (see Section 3)
• mhma.us/events — Events calendar page (full upcoming events list)
• mhma.us/prayer — Dedicated prayer times page with monthly PDF download
• mhma.us/volunteer — Volunteer signup and opportunities
• mhma.us/newsletter — Newsletter signup + archive of past issues
• mhma.us/programs — Organized programs directory (expand existing page)
• mhma.us/zakat — Zakat and sadaqa information page (already exists — improve)
5.3 Footer Redesign
• Add physical address of Unity Center / MHMA
• Add contact phone number and email
• Add newsletter signup field directly in footer
• Organize footer columns: Quick Links | Programs | Get Involved | Contact
• Add 501(c)(3) EIN and tax-exempt statement (critical for donors)
• Add Guidestar/Candid platinum seal if eligible (see MCABayArea.org)

6. Donation &amp; Fundraising UX
Donation user experience is where MHMA is most behind peers. The current site uses a single
Stripe link with no context, no goal tracking, and no multiple payment options. Every dollar of friction
in the donation flow costs real fundraising revenue.
6.1 Donation Page Redesign (mhma.us/donate)
• Add giving designation options: General Fund, Masjid Construction, Zakat, Sadaqa, Maktab
Support
• Add recurring donation option (monthly giving) — VRIC&#39;s &#39;Ansar Club&#39; is an excellent model
• Display multiple payment methods: Stripe/Card, Zelle, Check, Cash at masjid
• Add suggested giving amounts: $25 / $50 / $100 / $250 / $500 / Custom
• Show &#39;Your donation is 100% tax-deductible&#39; with EIN number
• Add employer matching information
• Add a &#39;Dedicate this donation&#39; option (in memory/honor of someone)
6.2 Recurring / Monthly Giving Program
• Create a named monthly giving program (e.g., &#39;MHMA Builders Club&#39;)
• Offer monthly sustainer amounts: $10 / $25 / $50 / $100 / $250 / month
• Promote with a dedicated landing page and homepage banner
• Send monthly impact email to sustainers
6.3 Donor Stewardship Features
• Automated donation receipt email with 501(c)(3) language
• Thank-you page after donation with social share buttons
• Quarterly donor newsletter with construction progress updates
• Annual donor report / impact summary page

7. Technical &amp; SEO Requirements
7.1 Performance
• Achieve Google PageSpeed score of 80+ on mobile (current WordPress theme may be slow)
• Compress and properly size all images — use WebP format
• Enable caching (WP Rocket or similar plugin)
• Remove unused CSS/JS (current theme appears to load heavy libraries)
7.2 Mobile Experience
• Full mobile audit — test on iPhone and Android at 375px and 390px widths
• Fix duplicate prayer time display on mobile
• Ensure donation CTAs are thumb-friendly (minimum 44px tap target)
• Prayer times widget should be readable on mobile without horizontal scroll
7.3 SEO
• Add meta descriptions to all pages (currently missing on homepage)
• Structured data markup for Organization and Event types
• Page titles should follow format: Page Name | MHMA | Mountain House
• Create a Google Business Profile if not already active
• Set up Google Search Console and verify sitemap
7.4 Accessibility
• All images require alt text
• Color contrast ratio must meet WCAG AA standards
• Form inputs must have associated labels
• Keyboard navigation must work throughout site
7.5 Integrations
• Prayer times: Integrate with MasjidAl API or IslamicFinder widget for auto-update
• Events: Consider The Events Calendar plugin (WordPress) — used by MCCEastBay
• Email: Connect newsletter signup to Mailchimp or similar
• Analytics: Verify Google Analytics 4 is properly configured with donation tracking as a
conversion event
• Donations: Keep Stripe but add Zelle info and check mailing address prominently

8. Phased Project Plan
The following phases prioritize fundraising impact first, then community engagement features, then
long-term optimization. Phase 1 should be completed before the next major fundraising event or
campaign push.

PHASE 1: FUNDRAISING FOUNDATION | 4–6 Weeks | Priority: CRITICAL
✓ Islamic Center Campaign Page (mhma.us/build) — Full dedicated page per Section 3
specs
✓ Live Fundraising Progress Bar — Embeddable widget with manual or API update
✓ Pledge System — Google Form or embedded form integration
✓ Donation Page Redesign — Multiple payment options, designations, suggested amounts
✓ Construction Campaign FAQ — Accordion format, 10–15 questions
✓ Homepage Hero Upgrade — New image/video, clear CTAs, remove duplicate prayer block
✓ Homepage Fundraising Banner — Mini progress bar and campaign link on homepage
✓ Footer: Add EIN + Tax-Exempt Statement — Critical for donor confidence

PHASE 2: COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT | 4–6 Weeks | Priority: HIGH
✓ Events Calendar Page — Full events listing, searchable, filterable by category
✓ Programs Directory Page — Grid layout with icon cards for all MHMA programs
✓ Newsletter Signup — Footer + dedicated page, connected to email platform
✓ Navigation Restructure — New nav with Build Our Masjid as top-level item
✓ Prayer Times: Auto-Sync Integration — Replace static times with API-driven widget
✓ Volunteer Page — Opportunities listing and signup form
✓ Community Stats Bar — Social proof numbers on homepage
✓ Monthly Giving Program Launch — MHMA Builders Club landing page and Stripe setup

PHASE 3: OPTIMIZATION &amp; GROWTH | Ongoing | Priority: MEDIUM
✓ Mobile Performance Audit &amp; Fix — PageSpeed 80+ on mobile target
✓ SEO Setup — Meta descriptions, structured data, Google Search Console

✓ Accessibility Audit — WCAG AA compliance review
✓ Blog / News Section — Construction updates, community stories
✓ Staff / Leadership Profiles — Imam, board members with photos
✓ Video Content Integration — YouTube embed on campaign page and homepage
✓ Annual Donor Report Page — Impact summary for donors
✓ TikTok / Modern Social Links — Add to footer and social section

9. Content MHMA Must Provide
The developer can build the infrastructure, but MHMA needs to supply the following content assets.
Preparing these in parallel with development will avoid delays.
Phase 1 Content (Needed Immediately)
• Architectural Rendering: High-resolution image of the planned Islamic Center exterior
• Campaign Overview Copy: 2–3 paragraphs explaining why MHMA needs a permanent
masjid
• Project Brochure: PDF of the full project brochure for download link
• Current Fundraising Total: Dollar amount raised to date, to seed the progress bar
• Campaign Goal Breakdown: Phase 1 / Phase 2 funding targets with explanations
• EIN Number: For all donation pages and receipt language
• Payment Info: Zelle email/phone, mailing address for checks
• FAQ Content: Answers to 10–15 frequently asked questions about the project
• Community Testimonials: 3–5 quotes from community members with permission to publish
Phase 2 Content
• Programs Descriptions: One paragraph + photo for each MHMA program
• Upcoming Events: Initial batch of 10+ events to populate the calendar
• Community Impact Stats: Years serving, families, youth in programs, etc.
• Staff/Imam Photo &amp; Bio: For leadership section
• Campaign Video: YouTube link or video file for embed on campaign page

